@startuml
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-SKILL)
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-STORE)
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-TARGET)
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-RENDER)
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-PROFILE-DOC)
' @id(CMP-DEPLOY-EXEC)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
' @ref(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE)
'
' Current-side ownership boundaries for /mdd-deploy as implemented.
' Canonical source of truth is crates/mdd-core/src/templates.rs; the
' .claude/.codex SKILL.md mirrors and .mdd/docs/deploy-profile.md are
' materialized by `mdd init` (Project::init_with_conflict_handler).
'
' CHANGE (cycle 0021): the skill gains an EXECUTION engine. After planning
' it invokes Bash to run az / terraform / docker against the LIVE Azure
' subscription, walking the generated runbook. Still OUTSIDE the parity
' gate — only now the skill runs the commands instead of handing them off.
'
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-SKILL, "Implemented: templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL + its SkillTemplate entry in templates::WORKFLOW_SKILLS, materialized into .claude/.codex/skills/mdd-deploy/SKILL.md. It PLANS (deployment diagram + runbook + generated IaC) and then EXECUTES that runbook to live traffic via CMP-DEPLOY-EXEC. A sibling of /mdd-render, outside the parity gate.")
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-STORE, "Specified by templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL: .mdd/deploy/<target>/ (diagram.puml + runbook.md), created on the first /mdd-deploy run. The runbook doubles as the execution plan the skill walks. Naturally outside /mdd-validate and /mdd-review scope, like the non-gated .mdd/map/ tree.")
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-TARGET, "Specified by templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL: the deployment target repo ../atlas-ate-server, read READ-ONLY for topology + security invariants; the generated infra/ (Bicep or Terraform) is written there at plan time and APPLIED from there at execute time.")
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-RENDER, "Implemented: the .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml tree is the Deploy branch of mdd_core::RenderTree (Project::render_sources), one of the trees the single `mdd render` command covers (DOM-RENDER-ENGINE), mirrored to .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL is a thin wrapper over `mdd render`. Additive, non-gating.")
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-PROFILE-DOC, "Implemented: .mdd/docs/deploy-profile.md, materialized from templates::deploy_profile_doc (MDD_DEPLOY_PROFILE_DOC) by Project::init_with_conflict_handler. Documents the azure-container-apps deployment-diagram conventions, the invariant checklist, and the execution model (auth, dry-run, autonomous-vs-irreversible step classification, halt-on-error, go-live gate).")
' @desc(CMP-DEPLOY-EXEC, "Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL Phase B: the execution engine — the skill (agent) invokes Bash to run az / terraform / docker against the LIVE Azure subscription, walking the generated runbook. Manages auth, dry-runs before any apply, runs idempotent steps autonomously, BLOCKS at irreversible steps and at go-live, and HALTS on the first failed step. NOT a new mdd CLI verb — execution is agent-driven Bash. Outside the parity gate. Realizes USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE.")
title /mdd-deploy ownership — plan + execute (current)

actor "Operator" as Op

component "/mdd-deploy\n(skill: plan + executor)" as Skill
component "/mdd-render\n(thin wrapper over `mdd render`)" as Render
component "execution engine\n(agent -> Bash: az / terraform / docker)" as Exec

folder ".mdd/deploy/azure-container-apps/\ndiagram.puml, runbook.md" as Store
folder "../atlas-ate-server/\ninfra/ (Bicep or Terraform)" as Target
folder ".mdd/rendered/deploy/\n**/*.svg" as Rendered
folder ".mdd/docs/deploy-profile.md" as ProfileDoc
cloud "Azure subscription\n(LIVE)" as Az

package "canonical source of truth" {
  component "crates/mdd-core/src/templates.rs\nMDD_DEPLOY_SKILL + WORKFLOW_SKILLS\n+ MDD_DEPLOY_PROFILE_DOC" as Templates
}

package "existing gated MDD pipeline\n(unaffected)" {
  component "/mdd-cycle / /mdd-validate /\n/mdd-review (parity gate)" as Gate
}

Op --> Skill : /mdd-deploy <description>
Templates ..> Skill : materialized by `mdd init`
Templates ..> ProfileDoc : materialized by `mdd init`
Skill --> Store : write diagram.puml + runbook.md (plan)
Skill --> Target : generate infra/ (plan)
Skill ..> ProfileDoc : follows conventions
Skill --> Exec : drive execution (walk the runbook)
Exec --> Store : read runbook.md as the execution plan
Exec --> Target : apply infra/ (terraform apply / az deployment)
Exec --> Az : auth, apply, provision secrets, migrate, route traffic
Op ..> Exec : auth handshake + confirm irreversible steps & go-live
Op --> Render : /mdd-render (or `mdd render` directly)
Render --> Store : `mdd render` reads .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml (Project-enumerated)
Render --> Rendered : write .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg (mirror)
Gate ..> Store : NEVER reads (outside the gate)

note bottom of Skill
  Plans, then EXECUTES the runbook via CMP-DEPLOY-EXEC.
  Now runs az / terraform / docker (the old "never runs
  az / docker / brew" non-goal is retired).
  Realizes USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE + USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE.
end note

note bottom of Exec
  Manages auth, dry-runs before apply, pauses only at
  irreversible steps + go-live, halts on first error.
  Agent-driven Bash — NOT a new mdd CLI verb. Outside the
  parity gate. Realizes USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE; go-live gated
  by OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-GOLIVE-CONFIRMED.
end note

note bottom of Gate
  /mdd-deploy is still decoupled: no objective<->current
  parity, no @sec parity. A deployment has no code-derived
  counterpart, so by design it is not routed into the gate
  — executing it instead of guiding it does not change that.
end note
@enduml
